<br>
For the last few weeks (maybe a month) I've noticed something crazy happening with my nukes.  I've been getting crits on an almost regular basis.  Now I know, you may be thinking &quot;Welcome to the wonderful world of AA crits&quot; but I still have yet to place my third AA into Run3, so I'm nowhere near that wonder of an AA branch.  Despite my lack of AA's, I've managed to sometimes go for 30 minutes where almost every other nuke that landed was a crit.  I've had rains crit on all three waves.  Where I might have previously gotten 2 or 3 crits per session I'm now getting 10, 15, or even 20.  I've tried speaking with other wizards on my server about this, so that I could maybe avoid unveiling something that the wizard community is just keeping under their non-pointy hats, however I've only gotten stories of a similar experience from one other wizard and he was on a different server than me.<br>
<br>
Are there any other wizards out there who have noticed this?  With SOE's ban without question policy I'm halfway afraid that I'm unknowingly exploiting some new bug in the game and will see a GM appear before me one day to strike me down for all my crimes.  Please, forgive me if I have sinned against the wizard community by speaking of this on a public forum, but noone else seems to be willing to talk about it.<br>
<br>
Xuakal Zilthane<br>
Level 59 Evoker<br>
